docs.name: Resources Land: Perm. meadows & pastures - Cultivated - Norway
docs.description: Some of the most interesting data for economists is found in this domain. The national distribution of land, among arable land, pastures and other lands, as well as the importance of irrigation are just some of the interesting data sets. The Agricultural Resources domain covers: Investment, Land and irrigation, Labour, Machinery, Fertilizers, Pesticides, Population. The Resources domain considers factors of production for the agricultural sector. Broadly speaking, this section details how countries differ in endowments of the three classic inputs: labour, land and capital. Qualitative differences are important for each but are particularly difficult to summarise in a single indicator for land, the productivity of which depends heavily on water and soil conditions.

docs.name: Percentage of enterprises evaluating the effect of CVT courses by type of evaluation and size class  : Percentage of total : Using indicators of any improvements in production : Ireland : 250 employees or more
docs.description:
CVTS2 and CVTS3 data were collected with reference year 1 1999 and 2005 and published by Eurostat in order to:
Provide the Commission with harmonised, reliable and relevant statistical information needed to define, implement, monitor and evaluate Commission policies in the continuing vocational training in enterprises sector.
Provide the EU institutions, national administrations, enterprises, professional associations and EU citizens with high quality statistical services and products in the field of training.
CVTS3 provides comparable statistics on training enterprises, the participation to training, the volume of CVT courses and its costs, and moreover information on Initial vocational training (IVT) courses.
CVTS2 provides comparable statistical results on training and non-training enterprises, the supply of and the demand for vocational skills, the need for CVT and the forms, content and volume of CVT, the use of enterprises' own training resources and of external providers, and the cost of CVT courses.
The CVTS1 was the first survey on continuing vocational training in enterprises carried out on the EU level in a co-ordinated form (outline questionnaire, common definitions, and common recommendations with the respect to the fieldwork). The survey therefore was of pioneering nature, and is not any longer disseminated.
Full metadata at: http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/cache/ITY_SDDS/EN/trng_cvts_esms.htm

docs.name: Total by species since 1977 area in hectares  : All varieties of apricots : Hungary
docs.description:
The domain FRUCTUS contains the results of surveys of areas under certain species of fruit trees (apples, pear, peach, apricot, orange, lemon, small-fruited citrus).
The statistical surveys on orchards are carried out by the Member States in order to determine the production potential of plantations of certain species of fruit trees.
The results presented in the data abse  give areas (in hectares) by variety and age and density classes
Data are grouped by "fruit tree species". The database is therefore structured around this parameter. Data on a particular "species" constitute a table.
Full metadata at: http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/cache/ITY_SDDS/EN/orch_esms.htm
